# KeyboardEngine

## Purpose

The **KeyboardEngine** module is responsible for storing and updating the current keyboard state.

It is the central part of the firmware logic and maintains an internal buffer representing the state of all keyboard outputs.

---

## Description

KeyboardEngine does not communicate directly with the hardware.

Its only responsibility is to update the internal keyboard buffer according to incoming MIDI messages.

The transfer of this buffer to the shift registers is handled by a separate module.

---

## Public Interface

The module provides functions for:

* initializing the internal buffer;
* pressing a key;
* releasing a key;
* clearing the buffer;
* returning a pointer to the buffer for use by other modules.

---

## Operating Principle

The internal keyboard buffer consists of six bytes.

Each bit represents one keyboard output.

When a **Note On** or **Note Off** message is received, the corresponding bit is updated.

After the buffer has been modified, its contents can be transferred to the ShiftRegisterDriver module.

---

## Limitations

Version 1.0 supports:

* 48 keyboard outputs;
* MIDI **Note On** messages;
* MIDI **Note Off** messages.

Velocity and other MIDI features are not implemented in this version.

